Privacy Policy for LeetCode to GitHub

Effective Date: 1/5/2025

LeetCode to GitHub ("the Extension") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how the Extension collects, uses, and safeguards your data.

1. Information We Collect

The Extension collects the following types of data:

Browsing History: The URLs of websites you visit.

Website Content: Text and metadata from web pages you access.

2. Purpose of Data Collection

The collected data is used exclusively to enhance your browsing experience by providing the features and functionality of the Extension. Examples include:

Checking if you are on LeetCode.com.

Scraping code from your LeetCode submissions.

3. Data Storage

Your data is securely stored in one of the following locations:

Local Storage: Data is saved directly on your device.

User-Controlled Cloud Storage: Data is saved to your Google Chrome cloud storage.

4. Data Security

We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. These measures include:

Secure access protocols for retrieving stored data.

Regular security audits and updates.

5. Data Sharing

The Extension does not share or sell your data to any third parties or external servers. The Extension transmits your data to Github.com when submissions are accepted on Leetcode.com. All data remains under your control. 

6. User Control

You have full control over your data. Features include:

Data Deletion: You can delete your data by uninstalling the extension and deleting the corresponding Github repository.

7. Childrenâ€™s Privacy

The Extension is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children.

8. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted within the Extension.

9. Your Consent

By using the Extension, you agree to this Privacy Policy.
